"  en: {\n    'nav.home': 'Home',\n    'nav.tuina': 'Tuina Massage',\n    'nav.diseases': 'Diseases',\n    'nav.ai_qna': 'AI Q&A',\n    'lang.select': 'Select Language',\n    'app.title': 'Sagdyn Çagalar',\n    'app.subtitle': 'A reliable platform for child health and care',\n    \n    'home.hero.title': 'Your Child’s Health is Our Priority',\n    'home.hero.subtitle': 'A comprehensive health platform with pediatric medical information, a Tuina massage guide, and an AI assistant.',\n    'home.hero.cta': 'Learn More',\n    'home.features.title': 'Our Features',\n    'home.feature.tuina.title': 'Tuina Massage',\n    'home.feature.tuina.desc': 'Ancient Chinese Tuina massage techniques to improve children\\'s immunity and health.',\n    'home.feature.diseases.title': 'Pediatric Diseases',\n    'home.feature.diseases.desc': 'Reliable information on all types of childhood diseases, symptoms, and treatments.',\n    'home.feature.ai.title': 'AI Assistant',\n    'home.feature.ai.desc': 'Ask any question about your child\\'s health and get an instant response from AI.',\n    \n    'tuina.title': 'Tuina Massage Guide',\n    'tuina.intro.title': 'What is Tuina massage?',\n    'tuina.intro.desc': 'Tuina is a branch of Traditional Chinese Medicine involving massage of specific acupoints on a child\\'s body to treat illnesses and boost immunity.',\n    'tuina.history.title': 'History and Origins',\n    'tuina.history.desc': 'Tuina massage has been a core component of Traditional Chinese Medicine (TCM) for over 2,000 years. It focuses on regulating the flow of \"Qi\" (vital energy) in the body and enhancing natural healing capabilities. The specialized pediatric form was refined during the Ming Dynasty (1368–1644).',\n    'tuina.science.title': 'Scientific Support',\n    'tuina.science.desc': 'Modern scientific research demonstrates that Tuina massage reduces pain in children, lowers stress hormones, and helps strengthen the immune system. Clinical trials show this method is particularly effective in alleviating cough and asthma symptoms.',\n    'tuina.testimonial.title': 'Parent Testimonials',\n    'tuina.testimonial.1.text': '\"After learning Tuina massage, my child\\'s sleep schedule completely improved. He sleeps peacefully through the night without waking up.\"',\n    'tuina.testimonial.1.author': '— Aygul S., mother of a 2-year-old',\n    'tuina.testimonial.2.text': '\"We suffered a lot from intestinal colic. Once we started daily abdominal massage, my baby relaxed and the crying decreased significantly.\"',\n    'tuina.testimonial.2.author': '— Merdan K., father of a 6-month-old',\n    'tuina.areas.title': 'Organs and Their Benefits',\n    'tuina.areas.desc': 'Tuina massage affects specific organs of the child, improving their normal functioning.',\n    'tuina.organ.1.name': 'Stomach and Intestines',\n    'tuina.organ.1.benefit': 'Improves digestion, relieves colic, increases appetite.',\n    'tuina.organ.2.name': 'Lungs and Respiration',\n    'tuina.organ.2.benefit': 'Treats colds, coughs, and makes breathing easier.',\n    'tuina.organ.3.name': 'Kidneys and Nervous System',\n    'tuina.organ.3.benefit': 'Improves sleep quality, restores natural immunity.',\n    'tuina.steps.title': 'Step-by-step Massage Technique',\n    'tuina.step.1.title': '1. Abdominal massage for digestion',\n    'tuina.step.1.desc': 'Lay the child on their back. Gently stroke the abdomen in circular clockwise motions around the navel (3-5 minutes). This eases digestion and relieves pain.',\n    'tuina.step.2.title': '2. Chest and back massage for lungs',\n    'tuina.step.2.desc': 'Stroke the chest from the center outwards with your palm. Then gently massage the back between the shoulder blades up and down (do not press on the bones).',\n    'tuina.step.3.title': '3. Spinal massage for immunity',\n    'tuina.step.3.desc': 'With your fingertips, stroke along the spine from bottom to top. Gently press the center of the child\\'s palms and soles with your thumb.',\n    'tuina.benefits.title': 'Health Benefits',\n    'tuina.benefit.1': 'Naturally boosts the immune system.',\n    'tuina.benefit.2': 'Improves digestion and promotes deeper sleep.',\n    'tuina.benefit.3': 'Relieves fever, cough, and common cold symptoms.',\n    \n    'diseases.title': 'Pediatric Diseases Library',\n    'diseases.fever': 'Fever & Infections',\n    'diseases.respiratory': 'Respiratory Diseases',\n    'diseases.skin': 'Skin Diseases',\n    'diseases.digestive': 'Digestive Issues',\n    'diseases.allergies': 'Allergies',\n    'diseases.category_select': 'Select a category',\n    'diseases.category_select_desc': 'to view diseases and treatments',\n    'diseases.categories.title': 'Categories',\n    'diseases.categories.desc': 'Choose a category below to explore common pediatric conditions, their symptoms, and suggested home care.',\n    'diseases.info.soon': 'Information will be added soon',\n    'diseases.label.symptoms': 'Symptoms',\n    'diseases.label.treatment': 'Treatment / Home Care',\n    'diseases.data.fever.1.name': 'Common Cold',\n    'diseases.data.fever.1.symptoms': 'Runny nose, low fever, cough',\n    'diseases.data.fever.1.treatment': 'Ensure hydration and rest. Use saline drops for congestion. Avoid OTC cough medicines for children under 4 without consulting a pediatrician.',\n    'diseases.data.fever.2.name': 'Flu (Influenza)',\n    'diseases.data.fever.2.symptoms': 'High fever, body aches, fatigue',\n    'diseases.data.fever.2.treatment': 'Administer pediatrician-approved antipyretics like acetaminophen. Seek immediate care for any respiratory distress or unusual lethargy.',\n    'diseases.data.digestive.1.name': 'Gastroenteritis',\n    'diseases.data.digestive.1.symptoms': 'Vomiting, diarrhea, stomach pain',\n    'diseases.data.digestive.1.treatment': 'Prioritize oral rehydration solutions (ORS) in frequent, small amounts. Gradually introduce a bland (BRAT) diet. Avoid dairy and sugary drinks.',\n    'diseases.data.respiratory.1.name': 'Asthma',\n    'diseases.data.respiratory.1.symptoms': 'Wheezing, shortness of breath, chest tightness',\n    'diseases.data.respiratory.1.treatment': 'Strictly follow prescribed Asthma Action Plan. Use short-acting inhalers for flare-ups. Mitigate environmental triggers like dust and pet dander.',\n    'diseases.data.respiratory.2.name': 'Bronchitis',\n    'diseases.data.respiratory.2.symptoms': 'Cough with mucus, fatigue, mild fever',\n    'diseases.data.respiratory.2.treatment': 'Use a cool-mist humidifier and high fluid intake to thin mucus. Consult a doctor if the cough persists beyond 2-3 weeks or worsens.',\n    'diseases.data.skin.1.name': 'Eczema',\n    'diseases.data.skin.1.symptoms': 'Dry, itchy, red patches on skin',\n    'diseases.data.skin.1.treatment': 'Apply unscented, thick emollients immediately after brief baths. Use prescribed topical corticosteroids during active flare-ups.',\n    'diseases.data.skin.2.name': 'Chickenpox',\n    'diseases.data.skin.2.symptoms': 'Itchy rash with blisters, fever, fatigue',\n    'diseases.data.skin.2.treatment': 'Apply calamine lotion or oatmeal baths for itch. Keep fingernails trimmed to prevent secondary bacterial infections. Administer acetaminophen (strictly avoid aspirin).',\n    'diseases.data.allergies.1.name': 'Seasonal Allergies',\n    'diseases.data.allergies.1.symptoms': 'Sneezing, runny nose, itchy eyes',\n    'diseases.data.allergies.1.treatment': 'Administer non-sedating, second-generation antihistamines. Utilize HEPA air purifiers and keep windows closed during high pollen seasons.',\n    \n    'qa.title': 'AI Medical Assistant',\n    'qa.subtitle': 'Ask anything about child health, diseases, or care.',\n    'qa.placeholder': 'Type your question here...',\n    'qa.send': 'Send',\n    'qa.error.empty': 'Sorry, no information found.',\n    'qa.error.connect': 'Error connecting to the AI assistant. Please try again later.',\n    'qa.disclaimer': '(I can speak Turkmen, Russian, English, and German)',\n    'qa.thinking': 'Thinking...',\n    'tuina.header.subtitle': 'Tuina is an ancient Chinese therapeutic massage technique that focuses on restoring balance and healing.',\n    'tuina.benefits.1': 'Improves circulation and promotes relaxation.',\n    'tuina.benefits.2': 'Alleviates muscle tension and joint pain.',\n    'tuina.benefits.3': 'Relieves stress and anxiety.',\n    'tuina.benefits.4': 'Helps with digestive and respiratory problems in children.',\n    'tuina.benefits.5': 'Improves flexibility and range of motion.',\n    'tuina.techniques.title': 'Common Tuina Techniques',\n    'tuina.tech.1.title': 'Kneading',\n    'tuina.tech.1.desc': 'Uses circular movements with the fingers to relax muscles and improve blood flow.',\n    'tuina.tech.2.title': 'Rolling',\n    'tuina.tech.2.desc': 'Gentle rolling movements along the limbs or spine to relieve stiffness and tension.',\n    'tuina.tech.3.title': 'Pressing',\n    'tuina.tech.3.desc': 'Applying direct pressure on key acupoints to stimulate energy flow and relieve pain.',\n    'tuina.steps.title2': 'How to Perform Tuina Massage: Step-by-Step',\n    'tuina.step2.1': 'Step 1: Start by having the child or patient lie comfortably on their back.',\n    'tuina.step2.2': 'Step 2: Begin with gentle, circular kneading motions on the shoulders to relax the muscles.',\n    'tuina.step2.3': 'Step 3: Use rolling motions on the back and spine to release tension.',\n    'tuina.step2.4': 'Step 4: Apply light pressure on acupoints along the meridians to restore balance.',\n    'tuina.step2.5': 'Step 5: End with soft, smooth strokes to calm the body and mind.',\n    'tuina.whentouse.title': 'When to Use Tuina Massage',\n    'tuina.whentouse.intro': 'Tuina is effective for children and adults alike in treating:',\n    'tuina.whentouse.1': 'Digestive issues like constipation or bloating.',\n    'tuina.whentouse.2': 'Respiratory conditions like asthma and cough.',\n    'tuina.whentouse.3': 'Muscle pain, stiffness, and joint issues.',\n    'tuina.whentouse.4': 'Stress relief, relaxation, and improving sleep quality.',\n    'tuina.children.title': 'Tuina for Children',\n    'tuina.children.desc': 'Tuina can be adapted for young children, offering gentle pressure and soothing techniques tailored to their needs. It is especially helpful for managing discomfort in children without the use of medications.',\n    'tuina.video.title': 'Watch the Video Tutorial',\n    'tuina.faq.title': 'Frequently Asked Questions',\n    'tuina.faq.1.q': 'Is it safe?',\n    'tuina.faq.1.a': 'Yes, Tuina is generally safe when performed by a trained professional, and is adapted to be very gentle for children.',\n    'tuina.faq.2.q': 'How long does a session last?',\n    'tuina.faq.2.a': 'A typical pediatric session lasts 15-30 minutes depending on the child\\'s age and condition.',\n    'tuina.faq.3.q': 'What can parents expect?',\n    'tuina.faq.3.a': 'Parents can expect their child to feel more relaxed and rested. It acts as a complementary therapy alongside conventional pediatric care.',\n    \n    'tuina.body.title': 'Body Parts and Techniques',\n    'tuina.body.1.title': '1. Head and Face',\n    'tuina.body.1.how': 'How to Perform It: Forehead: Use your fingers to rub gently in small circular motions on the forehead. Temples: Lightly massage in circles on both temples. Around the Eyes: Gently press around the eyes and eyebrows to relieve tension.',\n    'tuina.body.1.benefits': 'Benefits: Relieves headaches, reduces eye strain, and helps calm the child.',\n    'tuina.body.1.when': 'When to Do It: Before bedtime to help the child relax. After screen time or any stressful activity to ease eye strain and stress.',\n    \n    'tuina.body.2.title': '2. Neck and Shoulders',\n    'tuina.body.2.how': 'How to Perform It: Neck: Use your thumbs to gently press and massage the muscles along the neck. Shoulders: Apply gentle circular motions on the shoulder muscles with your palms.',\n    'tuina.body.2.benefits': 'Benefits: Reduces tension in the neck and shoulders, helps with posture, and relieves stress.',\n    'tuina.body.2.when': 'When to Do It: After long periods of sitting or playing. When the child feels tense or stressed.',\n\n    'tuina.body.3.title': '3. Arms and Hands',\n    'tuina.body.3.how': 'How to Perform It: Arms: Rub up and down the forearms with light strokes. Hands: Massage the palms and fingers gently with your thumbs, using circular motions.',\n    'tuina.body.3.benefits': 'Benefits: Improves circulation, enhances flexibility, and reduces tension in the hands.',\n    'tuina.body.3.when': 'When to Do It: After writing or using devices. Before or after sports to help with flexibility.',\n\n    'tuina.body.4.title': '4. Back and Spine',\n    'tuina.body.4.how': 'How to Perform It: Spine: Gently massage along the spine, moving from the neck to the lower back with your thumbs or fingertips. Lower Back: Apply light pressure on the lower back and gently move your palms in circular motions.',\n    'tuina.body.4.benefits': 'Benefits: Relieves back pain, helps improve posture, and promotes relaxation.',\n    'tuina.body.4.when': 'When to Do It: After physical activities like sports or play. After long sitting periods to reduce tension in the back.',\n\n    'tuina.body.5.title': '5. Legs and Feet',\n    'tuina.body.5.how': 'How to Perform It: Feet: Massage the soles and toes gently with your thumbs, using small circles. Legs: Use long strokes to massage from the feet to the thighs. Gently press on the calves and thighs.',\n    'tuina.body.5.benefits': 'Benefits: Reduces leg cramps, improves blood circulation, and supports healthy growth.',\n    'tuina.body.5.when': 'When to Do It: Before or after physical activities like running or playing sports. Before bedtime to help the child relax and sleep better.',\n\n    'tuina.timing.title': 'When Should Tuina Massage Be Done?',\n    'tuina.timing.daily': 'Daily Use: Tuina can be performed daily to maintain relaxation and promote overall health.',\n    'tuina.timing.special': 'Special Times: After physical activities like sports or play. When the child feels stressed, tense, or has muscle pain. To help with sleep issues, headaches, or digestive discomfort.',\n\n    'tuina.keybenefits.title': 'Key Benefits of Tuina Massage for Children',\n    'tuina.keybenefits.health': 'Health Benefits: Helps with blood circulation, supports immune function, and improves overall health.',\n    'tuina.keybenefits.relieves': 'Relieves Common Problems: Eases muscle tension, stress, headaches, and digestive issues.',\n    'tuina.keybenefits.sleep': 'Improves Sleep: Promotes relaxation and helps children sleep better.',\n\n    'footer.text': '© 2026 Sagdyn Çagalar. All rights reserved. Disclaimer: This website is for informational purposes only and does not replace professional medical advice.',\n  },\n"